Often, resources fetched through the API will not expand their sub resources by default (such
as a transactions's customer will not be expanded by default). This behaviour can be
overridden using the expand option. For example, expanding the Transaction's
Customer can be done by setting `expand` to `customer`.

It is also possible to expand nested sub resources by using the dot notation.
To expand the Subscriptions of a Customer in a Transaction, you can set
`expand` to `customer.subscriptions`.

Multiple expansions can also be done within a single request by providing them
in the `expand` array.
